      • parseArguments

        public boolean parseArguments(java.lang.Object obj,
                              java.lang.String... args)
        Deprecated. Use parseArguments(boolean, String, boolean, Object, String...) instead.
        Parse given string array, and set the fields that are annotated with a CmdArgument annotation from the given object. Supported data types are Boolean, String, Integer, Float, Double, Long and the listed primitive counterparts.

        Syntax:
        - Boolean fields prefix the key with plus(+) for true, or prefix a hyphen(-) for false.
        - Value fields prefix the key with double hyphens (--) followed by a space and the value.

        Parameters:
        obj - The object to look for fields and apply values to fields.
        args -
        Returns:
        false if parsing failed.

      • parseArguments

        public boolean parseArguments(boolean displayHelp,
                              java.lang.String programDescription,
                              boolean displaySyntax,
                              java.lang.Object obj,
                              java.lang.String... args)
        Parse given string array, and set the fields that are annotated with a CmdArgument annotation from the given object. Supported data types are Boolean, String, Integer, Float, Double, Long and the listed primitive counterparts.

        Syntax:
        - Boolean fields prefix the key with plus(+) for true, or prefix a hyphen(-) for false.
        - Value fields prefix the key with double hyphens (--) followed by a space and the value.

        Parameters:
        displayHelp - If true generated help will be displayed if an error occured.
        programDescription - The description that will be used in the generated help. Set to null or empty to disable description.
        displaySyntax - If true the syntax will be displayed within the generated help.
        obj - The object to look for fields with CmdArgument annotation.
        args -
        Returns:
        false if parsing failed.

      • parseArguments

        public boolean parseArguments(boolean displayHelp,
                              java.lang.String programDescription,
                              boolean displaySyntax,
                              java.lang.Object obj,
                              java.lang.Object[] ignoreObjs,
                              java.lang.String... args)
        Parse given string array, and set the fields that are annotated with a CmdArgument annotation from the given object. Supported data types are Boolean, String, Integer, Float, Double, Long and the listed primitive counterparts.

        Syntax:
        - Boolean fields prefix the key with plus(+) for true, or prefix a hyphen(-) for false.
        - Value fields prefix the key with double hyphens (--) followed by a space and the value.

        Parameters:
        displayHelp - If true generated help will be displayed if an error occured.
        programDescription - The description that will be used in the generated help. Set to null or empty to disable description.
        displaySyntax - If true the syntax will be displayed within the generated help.
        obj - The object to look for fields with CmdArgument annotation.
        ignoreObjs - CmdArguments within the object will be ignored, and will prevent help being displayed.
        args -
        Returns:
        false if parsing failed.

      • generateHelp

        public static java.lang.String generateHelp(java.lang.String programDescription,
                                            boolean displaySyntax,
                                            java.lang.Object... classObjects)
        Generates a formatted string containing the arguments available, from the specified objects.
        Parameters:
        programDescription - a description that is prefixed to the start of the help string.
        displaySyntax - if true the syntax of how to set argument values will be added to help string.
        classObjects - The objects that the CmdArgument annotations will be extracted from, using createKeyToFieldsMap(Object).
        Returns:
        a formatted help string ready to be printed to the console.
        See Also:
        CmdArgument, createKeyToFieldsMap(Object)
